export const METHODOLOGY = "##\nHow much water should I drink in a day?\nUntil your urine is clear. Some people need 2 liters of water, others\nmore, and others less. Although the general rule is 30ml per kg of\nbody weight, it depends on how well your kidneys are functioning.\nThat's why I usually recommend evaluating by the color of your urine.\nIn the morning, it's normal for it to be more yellow, but the goal is\nto go to bed with the last urine of the day looking like water, that\nis, clear! Remember that the color can vary if you are taking\nmedications or B-complex vitamins, so a minimum of 2 liters of water\nper day is okay? It's not juice, soda, or tea, it's water! Teas can be\nan additional hydration tool during the day therapeutically.\nI am new to eating healthy, where should I begin?\n### **The #dietitianproud Plate**\nThe #thedietitianproud plate is as colorful as possible with natural\ningredients, meaning avoiding processed foods and consuming more leaves,\nvegetables, and fruits. Use extra virgin olive oil as the base of your\ndiet. For cooking, use an acidity of 0.5 (it will be written on the\nolive oil bottle), and for finishing preparation like soups or adding to\nsalads and sauces, use an acidity of 0.4 or lower. This helps to\npreserve the properties of the oil when cooking rice, grilling chicken,\nfor example. Prefer local, organic foods whenever possible. Drink more\ndigestive teas like fennel, ginger, chamomile, and lemongrass between\nmeals. When eating out, choose restaurants that offer fresh food, such\nas sourdough bread, fresh pasta, homemade burgers, and so on. Value the\nfood of your region and culture! Healthy eating is not just about\nnutrients; it is also about pleasure, culture, and entertainment. Avoid\nfried foods and foods with INS and other chemical additives.\n**Do you recommend counting calories?** I advocate for the quality of\nthe diet and the specification of the therapeutic properties of food for\neach case. Of course, calories matter in a weight management process.\nBut have you ever thought about comparing a zero-calorie soda with\norange juice? The soda would seem better because it has zero calories,\nbut what about the quality of what you\\\\'re consuming? It has artificial\nsweeteners and acidity that can harm your bones, stomach, and cause\ninflammation. Natural orange juice, on the other hand, has more calories\nbut also contains vitamins, antioxidants, and can be used before a\nworkout to give you energy. Calories can be compensated with exercise,\ninflammation cannot!\n**What is the best diet for losing weight?** The best answer is: the one\nyou will follow and, preferably, one that is based on your genetics and\ncurrent hormonal situation. Therefore, having this data is highly\nvaluable for efficient weight loss and to avoid frustrations and the\nfamous \\\\\"yo-yo effect.\\\\\" For instance, some obese people have low\ndopamine levels, which is our brain\\\\'s messenger for focus, motivation,\ndetermination. Fat cells in large quantities inhibit this messenger,\nmaking it so hard to stick to the diet and leading us to give up more\nquickly. In such cases, a diet rich in dopamine-boosting foods will be\nmore effective than a ketogenic or low-carb diet.\nFor people with a gene called FABP2, which involves \\\\\"stubborn fat,\\\\\"\nmerely restricting calories does not work; it requires high levels of\nantioxidants such as teas, berries, extra virgin olive oil, and physical\nactivity.\nBut generally, if you don\\\\'t know where to start, go for a diet with 30%\nprotein, 30% fat, and 40% carbohydrates, based on a caloric intake of 20\nkcal per kg of body weight, always focusing on the quality of healthier\nfoods to make up this diet.\n**Is diet soda really that bad for me?** Yes!!! Opt for flavored water,\nsparkling water with lemon, or teas with carbonated water, but avoid\nsoda as much as possible. Despite having zero calories, its acidity\nharms your stomach and intestines\\\\' ability to maintain good bacteria\ncapable of managing your immunity and disease prevention, as well as\nnutrient absorption, and it also harms your bones.\n**Should I practice intermittent fasting? I\\\\'m not sure if it\\\\'s better\nto eat smaller, more frequent meals or 3 larger meals.** Fasting should\nbe evaluated according to the patient\\\\'s genetics. Generally, if you\ndon\\\\'t have your genetic test, practice fasting twice a week on\nnon-consecutive days, such as Tuesday and Saturday, for 16 to 18 hours\nonly. Do not go for 24 hours or spend days without eating. And remember\nto hydrate well during fasting! Note: If you are experiencing a\nsignificant amount of stress or have a diagnosed eating disorder, do not\nfast as it can worsen your condition since the hormones released\nactivate cortisol and increase your stress. In the case of binge eating,\nyou emotionally feel deprived, and when you break the fast, you end up\nmaking unhealthy dietary choices. Remember, the post-fasting meal should\nbe light, high in protein, low in fat, and sugar-free, of course, always\nadding healthy foods---no burgers and fries!\n**What is the recommended amount of exercise per week?** Hey! Let\\\\'s get\nmoving! Did you know that physical exercise improves blood circulation,\nreduces the risk of cardiovascular diseases, helps control body weight,\nand promotes physical and mental well-being, among other benefits? But\nremember, don\\\\'t engage in an activity that you don\\\\'t enjoy, okay? You\ncan dance, cycle, lift weights, swim, play volleyball, or any activity\nyou like that isn\\\\'t a burden for you. Ideally, move your body every\nday, not necessarily lifting weights every day. You can alternate with\nexercises for your joints and strengthening, 2 to 3 times a week, like\nPilates. You can do aerobic exercises like walking, running, dance\nclasses, or martial arts, swimming, 3 times a week, but whenever\npossible, include weight training, which is a complete exercise for\nhealth, 3 times a week.\n**How can I boost my metabolism?** By drinking more water, i.e., staying\nwell hydrated. Engaging in regular physical activity. Incre";

export const RECIPES = "\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: ANSIEDADE, ESTRESSE, INS\u00d4NIA, P\u00c2NICO, OCD, PTSD, PREOCUPA\u00c7\u00c3O EXCESSIVA ===\n### Immunity Seasoning Mix for Anxiety\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 bunch of parsley\n\n-   1 bunch of green onions\n\n-   1/2 tray of thyme (only the leaves)\n\n-   100 ml olive oil\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Chop all the ingredients finely and process them into a paste.\n\n2.  Store in the refrigerator for up to 2 months.\n\n3.  Can be used as a base for various preparations: rice, meat, fish,\nstir-fries, and vegetables.\n\n### Flaxseed Gel (Egg Substitute)\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 cup flaxseeds\n\n-   2 cups water\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Soak the flaxseeds in water for 15 minutes.\n\n2.  Process until it forms a gel.\n\n3.  Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.\n\n### Brazil Nut Cream Cheese\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 cup broken Brazil nuts\n\n-   1/2 cup filtered water\n\n-   2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n-   Juice of 1/2 lime\n\n-   Salt to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Soak the Brazil nuts in water for at least 6 hours. Drain.\n\n2.  Blend the soaked nuts with the other ingredients until smooth.\n\n3.  Optionally, add fresh herbs or spices.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (2 tablespoons):**\n\n-   Calories: 100 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 2 g\n\n-   Protein: 2 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 9 g\n\n### Savory Granola\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 cup rolled oats\n\n-   2 tablespoons golden flaxseeds\n\n-   1 tablespoon toasted sesame seed mix\n\n-   1/2 tablespoon chia seeds\n\n-   1/2 cup chopped Brazil nuts\n\n-   2 tablespoons sliced almonds\n\n-   1/2 cup walnuts\n\n-   1/2 cup cashews\n\n-   1 teaspoon rosemary\n\n-   1 tablespoon dehydrated garlic\n\n-   2 tablespoons dehydrated onion flakes\n\n-   1 teaspoon thyme\n\n-   2 tablespoons olive oil\n\n-   Salt and black pepper to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Mix all ingredients in a bowl.\n\n2.  Spread on a baking sheet and bake at 180\u00b0C for 10 minutes.\n\n3.  Stir and bake for another 10 minutes.\n\n4.  Let cool and store in an airtight container.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (30g):**\n\n-   Calories: 150 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 12 g\n\n-   Protein: 4 g\n\n-   Fiber: 3 g\n\n-   Fats: 10 g\n\n### Avocado Mayonnaise\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 medium ripe avocado\n\n-   1/2 bunch chopped green onions\n\n-   Juice of 1/2 lime\n\n-   1 clove garlic, minced\n\n-   1 tablespoon yellow mustard\n\n-   1/2 cup olive oil\n\n-   Salt to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Blend all ingredients except olive oil until smooth.\n\n2.  With the blender running, slowly add the olive oil until creamy.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (2 tablespoons):**\n\n-   Calories: 80 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 2 g\n\n-   Protein: 1 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 8 g\n\n### Herb Paste\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   200 g ricotta\n\n-   2 tablespoons seasoning mix\n\n-   50 ml almond or cashew milk\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Blend all ingredients until creamy.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (2 tablespoons):**\n\n-   Calories: 60 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 1 g\n\n-   Protein: 3 g\n\n-   Fiber: 0 g\n\n-   Fats: 5 g\n\n### Chimichurri\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 bunch parsley\n\n-   1 bunch chives\n\n-   1 sprig rosemary\n\n-   10 sprigs thyme\n\n-   2 tablespoons oregano\n\n-   5 cloves garlic, minced\n\n-   1/2 onion\n\n-   1 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes (optional)\n\n-   1 tablespoon smoked paprika\n\n-   200 ml olive oil\n\n-   400 ml water\n\n-   Juice of 1 lime\n\n-   Salt to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Finely chop herbs and onion.\n\n2.  Mix all ingredients in a bowl, adjust salt.\n\n3.  Store in a jar in the refrigerator.\n\n4.  Emulsify and serve 15 minutes before use.\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: SA\u00daDE CARDIOVASCULAR, COLESTEROL ALTO, PRESS\u00c3O ALTA, TRIGLICER\u00cdDEOS, LDL, HDL, RISCO CARD\u00cdACO ===\n### Asian Turkey Cabbage Boats\n*Rende 6 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 \u00be--1 cup)*\n\n-   3 tablespoons fresh lime juice\n\n-   1 tablespoon cornstarch\n\n-   \u00bc cup coconut aminos\n\n-   1 teaspoon sesame oil\n\n-   1 tablespoon coconut oil\n\n-   1 pound ground turkey breast\n\n-   1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger root\n\n-   2 cloves fresh garlic, minced\n\n-   1 cup (\u2248 1 bunch) thinly sliced green onions\n\n-   1 small jalape\u00f1o pepper, finely chopped (optional)\n\n-   \u00bd to 1 cup sliced red bell pepper (1-inch strips)\n\n-   1 package shredded carrots (\u2248 2 cups)\n\n-   1 package broccoli slaw (\u2248 2 cups)\n\n-   1 tablespoon chopped fresh mint\n\n-   2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro\n\n-   6 Chinese cabbage leaves, lightly steamed for 1--2 minutes\n\n-   \u00bc cup chopped almonds, roasted\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  In a small bowl, mix together fresh lime juice, cornstarch, coconut\n    aminos, and sesame oil, and set aside.\n\n2.  In a large skillet or wok, heat coconut oil over medium-high heat.\nAdd ground turkey breast, ginger, and garlic, and cook. Stir often\nuntil turkey is browned and cooked through, about 6--8 minutes.\n\n3.  Add green onions, jalape\u00f1o, bell peppers, shredded carrots, and\nbroccoli slaw, and stir-fry until vegetables are crisp, but\ntender.\n\n4.  Add the lime juice-cornstarch mixture to the meat and vegetables.\n    Mix thoroughly, and turn down heat to low setting. Fold in chopped\n    mint and cilantro.\n**5.**. Arrange steamed Chinese cabbage leaves on a por\u00e7\u00e3o platter.\nSpoon about \u00be--1 cup of mixture onto each leaf.Top with chopped\nalmonds\n> **Tips:** As an alternative to the steamed Chinese cabbage, use butter\nor green leaf lettuce for lettuce wraps when por\u00e7\u00e3o this vegetable\nrich dish. There is no need to steam if using lettuce leaves so saves\na step in the preparation.\n\n### Balsamic Roasted Beets\n*Rende 2 por\u00e7\u00f5es*\n\n-   1 bunch trimmed beets (about 4 beets)\n\n-   1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar\n\n-   2 pinches sea salt\n\n-   2 pinches black pepper\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Preheat oven to 400\u00b0 F.\n\n2.  Gently scrub beets, and pat dry.Wrap in foil, and roast until tender\n(about 1 hour). Let cool, then peel and dice.\n\n3.  Place beets in a medium bowl, toss with balsamic vinegar, sea salt\nand pepper, and serve.\n\n### Black Soy Bean Cocoa Soup with Lime Zest\n*Rende 4 por\u00e7\u00f5es*\n\n-   1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil\n\n-   1 small red onion, chopped\n\n-   3 cloves garlic, pressed\n\n-   1 large carrot, chopped\n\n-   1 stalk celery, chopped\n\n-   3 cups low-sodium organic vegetable broth (or chicken broth)\n\n-   2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder\n\n-   1 teaspoon cumin\n\n-   1 cup canned black beans, drained and rinsed\n\n-   1 cup canned black soy beans, drained and rinsed\n\n-   Grated zest of 1 lime\n\n-   2--4 tablespoons fresh cilantro, chopped\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  In a medium saucepan, heat olive oil over low heat. Add the onion\n    and saut\u00e9 until the onions are caramelized, for approximately 15\n    minutes.\n\n2.  Add the pressed garlic, carrots, and celery, and cook for 5 minutes\nlonger.\n\n3.  Add the broth, cocoa powder, and cumin. Stir well, and simmer for 10\nmore minutes.\n\n4.  Stir in the black beans and black soy beans. Add lime zest. Cook for\napproximately 20 minutes longer, over low heat.\n\n5.  Serve warm, garnished with chopped cilantro.\n**Tips:** This recipe is wonderful topped with sliced avocado or fresh\nguacamole but this added ingredient is not part of this nutritional\nanalysis.\n\n### Chia Pomegranate Oatmeal\n*Rende 2 por\u00e7\u00f5es*\n\n-   1\u2153 cups water\n\n-   \u2154 cup rolled oats (old fashioned)\n\n-   1 pinch sea salt\n\n-   \u00bd cup liquid egg whites\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon cinnamon\n\n-   2 teaspoons chia seeds\n\n-   \u00bd cup pomegranate seeds\n\n#\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: DEPRESS\u00c3O, HUMOR BAIXO, MOTIVA\u00c7\u00c3O, DOPAMINA, SEROTONINA, N\u00c9VOA MENTAL ===\n### Immunity Seasoning Mix\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   100 g fresh ginger\n\n-   100 g turmeric root\n\n-   5 cloves of garlic\n\n-   100 ml olive oil\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Peel the ginger, turmeric, and garlic.\n\n2.  Finely chop all ingredients and process into a paste.\n\n3.  Store in the refrigerator for up to 2 months.\n\n4.  Use as a base for various preparations: rice, meat, fish,\nstir-fries, and vegetables.\n\n### Vegan Bread\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   20 g oat flour\n\n-   10 g almond flour\n\n-   5 g chia flour\n\n-   1 tablespoon flaxseed gel\n\n-   1/4 teaspoon xanthan gum\n\n-   1/4 teaspoon psyllium husk\n\n-   1/4 teaspoon salt\n\n-   20 ml olive oil or avocado oil\n\n-   20 ml water\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Mix the dry ingredients in a bowl.\n\n2.  In another bowl, mix the flaxseed gel with olive oil and water. Add\nthe dry ingredients and mix to combine.\n\n3.  Pour into a small greased bread pan and bake in a preheated oven at\n180\u00b0C for 30-40 minutes.\n\n4.  Let cool before slicing.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   Calories: 120 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 6 g\n\n-   Protein: 3 g\n\n-   Fiber: 2 g\n\n-   Fats: 10 g\n\n### Flaxseed Gel (Egg Substitute)\n**Ingredientes:**\n\n-   1 cup flaxseeds\n\n-   2 cups water\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Soak the flaxseeds in water for 15 minutes.\n\n2.  Process until it forms a gel.\n\n3.  Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.\n\n### Tofu and Carrot Spread\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   50 g tofu\n\n-   1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n-   Zest of 1/4 lime\n\n-   1/4 carrot, grated\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Blend the tofu, olive oil, salt, and lime zest until smooth.\n\n2.  Stir in the grated carrot.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   Calories: 70 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 2 g\n\n-   Protein: 3 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 6 g\n\n### Whey Protein Shake\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   250 ml cold almond milk\n\n-   1/2 banana\n\n-   1 tablespoon vanilla whey protein\n\n-   1/4 teaspoon matcha\n\n-   1 tablespoon 100% cocoa powder\n\n-   1 tablespoon molasses\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Blend all ingredients and serve cold.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   Calories: 150 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 20 g\n\n-   Protein: 12 g\n\n-   Fiber: 4 g\n\n-   Fats: 3 g\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: DETOX, DESINTOXICA\u00c7\u00c3O, F\u00cdGADO, ENZIMAS HEP\u00c1TICAS ALTERADAS, TOXINAS, ESTEATOSE ===\n### Almond Cocoa Smoothie\n*Rende 2 por\u00e7\u00f5es*\n\n-   2 cups unsweetened almond milk\n\n-   1 scoop vegan protein powder\\\\*\n\n-   1 small avocado\n\n-   1 tablespoon cocoa powder\n\n-   1 teaspoon almond extract\n\n-   \u00bd cup ice cubes\n\n-   Stevia, to taste (optional)\n\n-   1--2 cups loosely packed chopped kale\n*\\\\*Soy-free.Typical varieties include rice, pea, hemp. Should be\nsweetened with stevia or unsweetened altogether. 1 scoop should be \u2248\n17g protein.*\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Put all ingredients in a blender in the order listed.\n\n2.  Blend all ingredients together in a blender starting on low speed\nand working up to high speed until smooth.\n\n3.  Add more or less ice to desired thickness.\n\n### Asian Salad\n*Rende 10 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 \u00bd--\u00be cup)*\n> **Salad:**\n\n-   1 medium head Napa cabbage, end cut off & cut into quarters\n\n-   8 ounces bean sprouts\n\n-   1 small jicama or daikon, peeled & sliced into thin pieces\n\n-   1 bunch green onions, thinly sliced, dark green ends discarded\n\n-   1 large red bell pepper, cut in half & sliced very thin\n\n-   1 stalk celery, sliced very thin\n\n-   \u00bd cup slivered almonds\n\n-   1 bunch cilantro, chopped (set aside several tablespoons for\n    garnish)\n**Dressing:**\n\n-   \u2154 cup grapeseed or olive oil\n\n-   \u2153 cup rice vinegar\\\\*\n\n-   1 tablespoon sesame oil\n\n-   3 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n\n-   1 clove garlic, minced\n\n-   3-inch piece fresh ginger\n\n-   1 teaspoon agave syrup\n\n-   2 pinches salt\n\n-   2 pinches black pepper\n*\\\\*Be sure to use unseasoned rice vinegar (no sugar added).*\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Whisk all dressing ingredients together and set aside.This can be\n    made up to several days ahead of time and stored in the\n    refrigerator.\n\n2.  Prepare the salad: **a.** Slice each quarter of cabbage very thin\n    and place into a large por\u00e7\u00e3o bowl.\n\n**b.** Add bean sprouts, jicama or daikon, green onion, pepper and\ncelery and mix well to combine.\n\n3.  Add half the cilantro and half the dressing and toss well. Allow to\nsit for a few minutes to blend.\n\n4.  Just prior to por\u00e7\u00e3o toss in almonds and garnish with remaining\n    cilantro.\n**Tips:** Add more dressing as needed, being careful not to make it\ntoo wet. The salad will become wetter as it sits; wait until por\u00e7\u00e3o\nbefore adding more if needed. Refrigerate if not por\u00e7\u00e3o immediately.\n\n### Asparagus and Kohlrabi Salad\n*Rende 6 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 1\u2154 cup arugula and \u2154 cup asparagus\nmixture)*\n\n-   1 pound asparagus, ends discarded\n\n-   2 medium Kohlrabi, peeled\n\n-   2 tablespoons olive oil, divided\n\n-   \u00bc pound arugula (or use \u00bd pound watercress)\n\n-   2 teaspoons balsamic vinegar\n\n-   1 pinch salt\n\n-   1 pinch black pepper\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Cut asparagus stalks into \u00bc-inch diagonal slices, separating tips.\n    Prepare kohlrabi by slicing in \u00bd-inch strips.\n\n2.  In a wok or large saut\u00e9 pan, stir-fry asparagus stalks and kohlrabi\nin\n1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat until slightly browned. Add\nasparagus tips and continue to stir-fry for another 4--5 minutes.\nRemove from heat and toss with salt and pepper.\n\n3.  Pile arugula (or watercress) in a salad bowl and toss with remaining\n1 tablespoon olive oil.Top with asparagus and kohlrabi, and\ndrizzle with balsamic vinegar. Serve immediately.\n\n### Balsamic Mustard Vinaigrette\n*Rende 10 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 2 tablespoons)*\n\n-   \u00bc cup balsamic vinegar\n\n-   \u00bc cup water\n\n-   1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n\n-   Herbs to taste\\\\*\n\n-   1 pinch sea salt\n\n-   1 pinch black pepper\n\n-   1 clove garlic, minced\n\n-   \u2153 cup cold-pressed, extra-virgin olive oil\n\n-   \u2153 cup flaxseed oil (or use all olive oil)\n*\\\\*Use dried rosemary, oregano, basil, parsley, tarragon, or any herb\nof choice.*\n\n#\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: CANSA\u00c7O, FADIGA, ENERGIA BAIXA, ANEMIA, TIREOIDE, HIPOTIREOIDISMO, FERRO BAIXO, B12 ===\n### Avocado Lime Soup\n*Rende 6 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 1 cup)*\n\n-   \u00bc cup fresh lime juice (juice of 2 limes)\n\n-   1\u00bd cup cucumber chunks\n\n-   1 stalk celery\n\n-   6 leaves Romaine lettuce\n\n-   1 avocado\n\n-   \u00bc cup fresh cilantro\n\n-   2 cups water\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon sea salt\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon cumin\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Using blender or food processor, blend together all ingredients\n    until smooth.\n\n2.  Serve cold. Garnish with extra chopped cilantro, if desired.\n**Tip:** For a variation, substitute the juice of 1 lemon for the lime\njuice, parsley for the cilantro, and hold the cumin.\n\n### Baby Greens with Blackberry Vinaigrette\n*Rende 2 por\u00e7\u00f5es*\n> **Dressing:**\n\n-   \u00bc cup fresh or frozen blackberries (defrost if frozen)\n\n-   1 teaspoon coarsely chopped shallots\n\n-   1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil\n\n-   2 teaspoons fresh lemon juice\n\n-   1 teaspoon balsamic vinegar\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon Dijon-style mustard\n\n-   1 pinch sea salt\n\n-   1 pinch freshly ground pepper\n**Salad:**\n\n-   4 cups lightly packed mesclun salad mix\n\n-   2 tablespoons crumbled fresh goat cheese\n\n-   3 tablespoons chopped walnuts\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Place all dressing ingredients in blender or mini food processor and\n    blend until dressing is creamy and smooth. Let dressing stand in\n    refrigerator for up to 24 hours before using.\n\n2.  When ready to serve salad, divide salad greens between 2 plates. Add\n    goat cheese, then drizzle 2 tablespoons of dressing over each\n    salad.Top with chopped walnuts.\n\n-   **Mito-Ketoflex and dairy-free options:** Omit goat cheese and\n    prepare as directed. Substitute cashew cheese for goat cheese if\n    desired. Note that nutritional analysis is calculated with dairy\n    ingredients included.\n\n### Baked Spinach Omelet\n*Rende 8 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o = one 3-inch by 4-inch piece)*\n\n-   \u00bc cup butter\n\n-   1 pound fresh spinach, washed\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon salt\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon pepper\n\n-   8 large eggs, beaten\n\n-   \u00be cup whole milk ricotta\n\n-   \u00bd cup heavy cream\n\n-   1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil (or \u00bd teaspoon dried basil)\n\n-   \u00be cup chopped plum tomatoes\n\n-   \u00be cup shredded whole milk mozzarella\n\n-   \u00bc cup thinly sliced scallions\n\n#\n\n### Directions\n1.  Preheat oven to 325\u00b0 F.\n\n2.  Melt butter in large skillet. Add fresh spinach, salt, and pepper.\n    Cook spinach until wilted. Set aside.\n\n3.  In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs and ricotta. Stir in cream and\nbasil. Fold in spinach, tomato, mozzarella, and scallions. Spread\nevenly in a greased baking dish (2-quart casserole or 12-inch by\n8-inch dish or equivalent).\n\n4.  Bake for 30--35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center\n    comes out clean. Allow to stand for 10--15 minutes before por\u00e7\u00e3o.\n**Tip:** This omelet makes a nice brunch dish and includes\nbrain-healthy spinach. In place of 1 pound of fresh spinach, you could\nuse a 10 ounce box of frozen spinach (thawed and squeezed dry).\n\n-   **Mito-Ketoflex and dairy-free options:** Omit ricotta and\n    mozzarella cheese, and substitute with almond or cashew cheese, if\n    desired. Substitute canned coconut milk for heavy cream and coconut\n    oil for butter.\nOmitting dairy still results in a vegetable omelet that tastes\nwonderful. Note that the nutrition analysis above includes the dairy\ningredients.\n\n### Basic Greens\n*Rende 6 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 \u00bd cup)*\n\n-   1 large bunch kale, collard greens, or bok choy, washed\n\n-   2--3 cloves garlic, minced or cut into slivers\n\n-   1 tablespoon olive or coconut oil\n\n-   \u00bd cup low-sodium vegetable or chicken broth\n\n#\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: SA\u00daDE FEMININA, TPM, MENOPAUSA, ENDOMETRIOSE, SOP, HORM\u00d4NIOS, FERTILIDADE, CICLO MENSTRUAL ===\n### STOVE-TOP GRANOLA\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   2 tablespoons shelled pumpkin seeds\n\n-   2 tablespoons unsweetened shredded coconut\n\n-   2 tablespoons cacao nibs or chopped almonds or walnuts\n\n-   2 tablespoons golden flaxseed meal\n\n-   3 tablespoons rolled oats\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon coconut oil\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon honey or molasses (optional)\n\nPreparation: Toast the oats in a skillet with coconut oil until lightly\nbrowned. Add the pumpkin seeds and toast until yellowish. Add the\ncoconut and stir until it starts to brown. Turn off the heat and mix in\nthe flaxseed meal, cacao nibs, and honey. Let it cool and store in a\nglass jar in the refrigerator.\n\nBenefits: Granola is an excellent source of fiber, protein, and healthy\nfats, along with antioxidants from the cacao nibs.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   Calories: 261.55 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 24.27 g\n\n-   Proteins: 7.59 g\n\n-   Fats: 16.34 g\n\n-   Fiber: 6.97 g\n\n### TOFU YOGURT\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   4-5 organic strawberries or \u00bc cup other red fruits\n\n-   \u00bd frozen banana\n\n-   25 ml plant-based milk or water (used coconut milk)\n\n-   50 g organic tofu\n\n-   1 teaspoon golden flaxseed\n\nPreparation: Blend all ingredients in a blender. Serve with a teaspoon\nof toasted pumpkin seeds on top.\n\nBenefits: Tofu is rich in phytoestrogens, helping with hormonal\nmodulation. It is important to use organic tofu to avoid pesticides.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   Calories: 78.05 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 3.13 g\n\n-   Proteins: 5.40 g\n\n-   Fats: 5.55 g\n\n-   Fiber: 2.18 g\n\n### PUMPKIN SEED MILK\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   \u00bc cup shelled pumpkin seeds\n\n-   1 cup warm water\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon natural vanilla extract\n\n-   \u00bd tablespoon white or black raisins\n\nPreparation: Soak the pumpkin seeds in water for 4-8 hours. Rinse and\nblend with warm water and raisins for about 5 minutes. Strain and mix in\nthe salt and vanilla. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.\n\nBenefits: Rich in essential nutrients, pumpkin seed milk is a great\nplant-based alternative with anti-inflammatory properties.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   Calories: 267.6 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 32.58 g\n\n-   Proteins: 14.7 g\n\n-   Fats: 11.64 g\n\n-   Fiber: 3.9 g\n\n### GOLDEN MILK FOR A GOOD MOOD\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   250 ml oat milk\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon turmeric powder\n\n-   A pinch of cinnamon powder\n\n-   A pinch of ginger powder\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon maca powder\n\n-   1 teaspoon golden flaxseed meal\n\n-   1 teaspoon honey\n\nPreparation: Heat the milk and mix in all the ingredients. Use a mixer\nfor a creamier texture.\n\nBenefits: This golden milk is known to improve mood and libido, and help\nprevent postpartum and menopause-related depression. Turmeric and maca\nare potent anti-inflammatories and mood regulators.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   Calories: 126.25 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 19.25 g\n\n-   Proteins: 2.06 g\n\n-   Fats: 5.595 g\n\n-   Fiber: 4.71 g\n\n### CARROT AND COCONUT PANCAKE\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   2 tablespoons oat flour\n\n-   1 teaspoon flaxseed meal\n\n-   1 teaspoon ground pumpkin seeds\n\n-   1 tablespoon unsweetened shredded coconut\n\n-   2 tablespoons grated organic carrot\n\n-   2 tablespoons water\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n-   A pinch of cinnamon powder\n\n-   1 teaspoon coconut sugar or molasses\n\nPreparation: Mix all ingredients by hand or in a blender. Pour\napproximately 2 tablespoons of batter into a lightly greased skillet\nwith coconut oil. Cook over low heat and flip when the edges lift from\nthe pan.\n\nBenefits: These pancakes are an excellent source of fiber and healthy\nfats, rich in beta-carotene from the carrot, which is a natural\nantioxidant.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   Calories: 164.0 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 19.0 g\n\n-   Proteins: 3.6 g\n\n-   Fats: 8.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 4.5 g\n\n### FIRST PHASE BREAD\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (2 slices):\n\n-   1 tablespoon shelled raw pumpkin seeds (6.25 g)\n\n-   1 tablespoon coconut flour (7.5 g)\n\n-   1 tablespoon fine or medium rolled oats (3.125 g)\n\n-   1 tablespoon brown rice flour (4.375 g)\n\n-   1 teaspoon ground flaxseed (3.3 g)\n\n-   \u215b teaspoon psyllium (0.625 g)\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon baking powder\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon yeast\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon brown sugar (1.25 g)\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n-   \u00bc cup water\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon apple cider vinegar\n\nPreparation: Mix all dry ingredients, except the yeast. Dissolve the\nyeast in warm water and let it grow. Add the activated yeast to the\ndough along with the rest of the water. Let it rest and bake in a\npreheated oven at 180\u00baC.\n\nBenefits: This bread is rich in fiber and healthy fats from the seeds\nand flours, aiding digestive and hormonal health.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o (2 slices):\n\n-   Calories: 184.25 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 23.5 g\n\n-   Proteins: 5.5 g\n\n-   Fats: 8.0 g\n\n-   Fiber: 6.0 g\n\n### DETOX PESTO\nIngredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   \u2159 bunch parsley\n\n-   \u2159 bunch cilantro (or another \u2159 bunch parsley)\n\n-   3 basil leaves\n\n-   1\u00bd teaspoons extra virgin olive oil\n\n-   1\u00bd teaspoons macadamia or avocado oil, or more olive oil\n\n-   1\u00bd teaspoons toasted shelled pumpkin seeds\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon cranberry or a small slice of apple\n\n-   \u00bd teaspoon lemon juice\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\nPreparation: Blend all ingredients in a blender until smooth. Store in a\nglass jar in the refrigerator.\n\nBenefits: This pesto is rich in antioxidants and healthy fats, aiding in\nbody detoxification and cardiovascular health.\n\nMacronutrients per por\u00e7\u00e3o:\n\n-   Calories: 132.5 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 1.0 g\n\n-   Proteins: 1.0 g\n\n-   Fats: 14.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 0.5 g\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: DOEN\u00c7AS AUTOIMUNES, HASHIMOTO, L\u00daPUS, ARTRITE REUMATOIDE, ESCLEROSE M\u00daLTIPLA, DOEN\u00c7A DE CROHN ===\n### Immunity Mix Seasoning\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   15 g fresh ginger\n\n-   15 g turmeric root\n\n-   1 clove of garlic\n\n-   15 ml olive oil\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Peel the ginger, turmeric, and garlic.\n\n2.  Combine all ingredients and process into a paste.\n\n3.  Store in the refrigerator for up to 2 months.\n\n4.  This paste can be used as a base for various dishes such as rice,\nmeat, fish, stir-fries, and vegetables.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (approximately 1 tablespoon or\n15 g):**\n\n-   Calories: 70 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 3 g\n\n-   Protein: 0.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 7 g\n\n### Flaxseed Gel (Egg Substitute)\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   15 g flaxseeds\n\n-   30 ml water\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Soak the flaxseeds in water for 15 minutes, then process until it\nforms a gel.\n\n2.  Store in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (approximately 1 tablespoon or\n15 g):**\n\n-   Calories: 25 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 1 g\n\n-   Protein: 1 g\n\n-   Fiber: 2 g\n\n-   Fats: 2 g\n\n### Cashew Cream Cheese\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   15 g raw, unsalted cashews\n\n-   7.5 ml filtered water\n\n-   1 teaspoon olive oil\n\n-   Juice of 1/4 lime\n\n-   Salt to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Soak the cashews in water until covered for at least 6 hours.\n\n2.  Drain the water and blend the cashews with the remaining ingredients\nuntil smooth.\n\n3.  Optional: Add fresh herbs or spices to taste.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (approximately 2 tablespoons\nor 30 g):**\n\n-   Calories: 75 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 3.5 g\n\n-   Protein: 1.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 0.5 g\n\n-   Fats: 6.5 g\n\n### Avocado Mayonnaise\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   25 g ripe avocado\n\n-   5 g chopped parsley\n\n-   Juice of 1/8 lime\n\n-   1/4 clove of garlic, minced\n\n-   1 teaspoon yellow mustard\n\n-   7.5 ml olive oil\n\n-   Salt to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients except the olive oil and blend\nfor a few minutes.\n\n2.  While blending, gradually add the olive oil until a creamy\nconsistency is achieved.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (approximately 2 tablespoons\nor 30 g):**\n\n-   Calories: 75 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 1 g\n\n-   Protein: 0.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 7 g\n\n### Tofu Mayonnaise\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   30 g tofu\n\n-   1 tablespoon olive oil\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n-   Zest of 1/4 lime\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Blend all ingredients in a food processor or mixer until creamy.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (approximately 2 tablespoons\nor 30 g):**\n\n-   Calories: 45 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 0.5 g\n\n-   Protein: 1 g\n\n-   Fiber: 0.5 g\n\n-   Fats: 4 g\n\n### Chimichurri\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   2 g parsley\n\n-   2 g chives\n\n-   0.5 g rosemary\n\n-   1 g thyme\n\n-   1/4 teaspoon oregano\n\n-   1 clove of garlic, minced\n\n-   2 g onion\n\n-   A pinch of red pepper flakes\n\n-   1/4 teaspoon smoked paprika\n\n-   15 ml olive oil\n\n-   30 ml water\n\n-   3.75 ml red wine vinegar\n\n-   Salt to taste\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Finely chop the herbs and onion.\n\n2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients, mix well, and adjust salt to\ntaste.\n\n3.  Store in a jar and refrigerate. Let sit at room temperature for 15\nminutes before por\u00e7\u00e3o, stirring well.\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (approximately 2 tablespoons\nor 30 g):**\n\n-   Calories: 70 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 1 g\n\n-   Protein: 0.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 7 g\n\n### Skillet Bread\n**Ingredients for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o:**\n\n-   1 tablespoon oat flour\n\n-   1/2 tablespoon flaxseed gel (see recipe)\n\n-   1/2 teaspoon baking powder\n\n-   A pinch of salt\n\n-   A dash of olive oil\n\n**Modo de preparo:**\n\n1.  Mix the flaxseed gel with the salt, then add the flour and finally\nthe baking powder.\n\n2.  Heat a non-stick skillet and pour the mixture over low heat.\n\n3.  Brown on both sides and serve.\n\n4.  Suggested accompaniment: unsweetened peanut butter and nuts\n(walnuts, macadamia, sunflower seeds).\n\n**Informa\u00e7\u00e3o nutricional for 1 por\u00e7\u00e3o (1 bread):**\n\n-   Calories: 50 kcal\n\n-   Carbohydrates: 6 g\n\n-   Protein: 1.5 g\n\n-   Fiber: 1 g\n\n-   Fats: 2 g\n\n\n=== RECEITAS TERAP\u00caUTICAS: INFLAMA\u00c7\u00c3O INTESTINAL, GASTRITE, REFLUXO, INTESTINO IRRIT\u00c1VEL, PERMEABILIDADE INTESTINAL, DISBIOSE ===\n### Directions\n1.  Put all ingredients in a blender in the order listed.\n\n2.  Blend, starting on low speed and working up to high speed, until\nsmooth.\n**Tips:** Discuss protein powders with your healthcare provider.\nSuggested varieties can include quality sources of bovine collagen,\npea, egg white, or hemp proteins. Use frozen berries instead of ice to\nmake smoothie cold and of desired thickness. (Frozen berries are not\nincluded in the nutritional analysis.)\n\n# Asian Beef Lettuce Wraps\n*Rende 4 por\u00e7\u00f5es (1 por\u00e7\u00e3o \u2248 3 lettuce wraps)*\n> ***(if beef is omitted)***\n\n-   1 tablespoon gluten-free tamari or coconut aminos\n\n-   \u00bc cup apple cider vinegar\n\n-   2 tablespoon fresh lime juice\n\n-   \u00bc teaspoon sea salt\n\n-   16 ounces grass-fed beef (organic preferred)\n\n-   1 teaspoon sesame oil\n\n-   \u00bd cup finely chopped onion\n\n-   3 cloves garlic, minced\n\n-   1 tablespoon peeled and minced fresh ginger\n\n-   1\u00bd cup carrots, cut into ";
